public interface InkObjectState
extends Proxiable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable

The interface of the base Ink state object. Every state object in Ink implements this interface (explicitly or implicitly).

Author:
Lior Schachter
See Also:
InkObject, InkObjectImpl

getBehavior

<B extends InkObject> B getBehavior()
Retrieves the behavior object of this state object. If the Ink class is defined with Java mapping "No Java", "State-Interface" or "State only", the behavior is inherited, i.e. the behavior object will be an instance of the behavior class of a superclass. The behavior object will be created and initialized on the first invocation of this method.

Returns:
the state object of this behavior object.

cloneState

<T extends InkObjectState> T cloneState()
Creates a deep clone of this object. The clone operation traverses the state object and creates a clone of every mutable object it encounters, such as inner state objects and collections. (Primitive values are immutable and therefore are shallow-copied.)
Object IDs are not cloned. The cloned state object and all its inner objects have unique IDs. Behavior objects are not created during this operation.

Returns:
a deep clone of this state object.

validate

boolean validate(ValidationContext context)
Validates this object by executing the validators from the constraints trait relevant to run-time system state. Equivalent to calling validate(context, SystemState.Run_Time). The messages reported during validation are collected into the context object.

Parameters:

Returns:
